HEADWORD: Tenebrous
<hw>Ten"e*brous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tenebrosus</ets>, fr. <ets>tenebrae</ets> darkness: cf. F.
<ets>t⟦eacute⟧n⟦eacute⟧breux</ets>.]</ety> <def>Dark; gloomy; dusky;
tenebrious.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Ten"e*brous*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The most dark, <qex>tenebrous</qex> night.</q> <rj><qau>J. Hall
(1565).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The towering and <qex>tenebrous</qex> boughts of the cypress.</q>
